    <!--
      Google Sign-In (Android). Unlike iOS — which reads `iosClientId` /
      `serverClientId` from capacitor.config.ts — the @codetrix-studio plugin
      resolves the Android client id as: config `androidClientId` → config
      `clientId` → THIS string resource `server_client_id`. We use the resource so
      the shared capacitor.config.ts stays iOS-only and untouched.

      The value is the WEB/server OAuth client id (same as capacitor.config.ts
      `GoogleAuth.serverClientId`), NOT an Android-type client id: `requestIdToken`
      is called with it, so the returned ID token's `aud` is the web client —
      which the backend allowlists as GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID (see poker/auth.py and
      flask_app/config.py GOOGLE_ALLOWED_AUDIENCES). It is a public client id, not
      a secret. Keep it in sync with capacitor.config.ts.

      NOTE: sign-in still requires an *Android-type* OAuth client (package
      com.mypokerface.app + the build's SHA-1 fingerprint) registered in Google
      Cloud Console, or Google returns status 10 (DEVELOPER_ERROR). See
      docs/guides/ANDROID_APP.md.
    -->
    <string name="server_client_id">637263623890-93qcchki4jp5ll80t0sra22b4qpjbit7.apps.googleusercontent.com</string>

